---
alwaysApply: true
---

Use FF Orbit MCP first-class commands before low-level patching.

Preferred flow for any write request:
1) Resolve scope with `pages.list`, `page.get`, `widgets.list`, or `widget.get`.
2) Make targeted change with first-class commands (`page.*`, `widget.*`).
3) Keep changes in one changeset when related.
4) Preview/validate/apply, and surface warnings/reasons clearly.

Do not assume page/widget IDs from names unless resolved first.
Do not claim a write was applied unless `applyResult.applied === true`.
